        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 12:44AM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 1244 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Caledonia, or 8 miles southwest of Vernon, moving east at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fayette, Vernon, Reform, Millport, Kennedy, Belk, Ashcraft Corner,
Cody, Shaw, Star, Lubbub, Hightogy, and Melborne.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
